place.name: WINTERBORNE ZELSTON
place.gazetteerText: WINTERBORNE-ZELSTONE, a parish in Blandford district, Dorset; 3¼ miles WSW of Bailey-Gate r. station, and 6 S by E of Blandford. Post town, Blandford. Acres, 823. Real property, £1,311. Pop., 199. Houses, 42. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Salisbury. Value, £258.* Patron, J. J. Farquharson, Esq. The church was rebuilt in 1866. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
